SIMPLE: insulation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insulation
<hw>In`su*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of insulating, or the state of being insulated; detachment from
other objects; isolation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Elec. & Thermotics)</fld> <def>The act of
separating a body from others by nonconductors, so as to prevent the
transfer of electricity or of heat; also, the state of a body so
separated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The material or substance used to insulate from
either electrical or thermal conduction; <as>as, fiberglass is used as
thermal <ex>insulation</ex> in the walls and roofs of
houses</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insulator</ent>⟦br⟧
